18:
Hm? Oh, it's you, Klaus. Can't a guy 
get a little shut-eye around here?
21:
What appalling negligence. Think 
how easy it would've been to kill you 
in your sleep.
24:
Hah! Yeah, yeah. I know a REAL killer 
when I see one, and you don't make 
the cut.
28:
I have come to wake you, as per the 
young mistress' orders.
34:
The silver-haired girl entrusted me 
with the task of waking you, so woken 
you shall be.
37:
You mean she ASKED you? Stella isn't 
the type to give orders. You can drop 
the henchman act, you know?
41: Also, what's that bag you've got there?
43:
Upon the chef's command, I have 
procured bell peppers, a pumpkin, 
and leeks.
48:
What, he sent you off to the grocery? 
Ahahaha, oh man, my sides! You 
make a better butler than assassin!
52:
Those were the orders, and they have
been executed. I fail to understand 
your amusement.
56:
Executed? I can't—
You're holding a big old bag of 
veggies. I just CAN'T take the evil 
henchman voice seriously!
60:
You are a king. Why do you forgo 
your birthright, your duty?
64:
My blades, my fangs... They are tools 
to be commanded as my liege 
desires!
67:
Rulers and servants, huh? Back in the 
desert, I was on the serving side of 
the equation.
69:
I know what it's like being ordered 
around. Being told to kill or be killed.
72:
Nothing. 'Cause I'm not letting others 
tell me who or what I am. I'm Nimbus.
Just Nimbus.
103:
I don't know what to do without orders
to fulfill, so I was thinking of potential 
tasks.
105:
I'm not much of a thinker, though, so 
this is all that came to mind.
108:
This? You mean training? 
...Wait, are you here to help me train?
111:
I don't know. But I will assist you, if you
so wish.
116:
If you wouldn't mind, that'd be 
amazing!
119:
I've never met a guy who could stab 
through wood with a leek!
123: A leek? Oh! I—I forgot I was holding it…
